# Domain Boundaries

## Domain ownership

| Domain | Owner documents | Owns |
|--------|-----------------|------|
| Product / workflow | `product-spec.md`, `source-of-truth.md`, `v1-scope.md` | Goals, workflow, inputs, outputs, V1 scope |
| Characters / continuity | `character-bible.md` | Nina & Nino, tiers, voice, appearance, age guardrails |
| Illustration prompts | `illustration-guide.md` | Prompt format, style, consistency rules |
| Architecture | `docs/phase-b-architecture-map.md` | Routes, data model, pipeline, folder structure |
| Drift / decisions | `drift-log.md` | Unresolved and accepted change decisions |

## MUST

- Change only the domain you are working in.
- Read the owning document before modifying behavior in that domain.
- Document cross-domain changes in `drift-log.md` before implementing.
- Extend lower-authority docs; do not contradict higher-authority docs.

## MUST NOT

- Change character rules while editing architecture, or vice versa, without documenting the cross-domain impact.
- Modify unrelated files "while you're there."
- Move domain knowledge into code comments instead of the owning document.
- Duplicate full spec content into rules, code, or new docs.

## Cross-domain change

If a change touches two or more domains: add a `drift-log.md` entry, update each affected document, then implement.
